<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-3-1" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Introduction</title>

  <!-- <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>Understand nth order linear differential equations</li>
    </ul>
  </objectives> -->


  <introduction>
    <p> The <m>n^{\text{th}}</m> order linear differential
      equations are of the form
      <me
        xml:id="eq-nonhomogeneous-0">
        \phi^{(n)}(x) + a_{n-1}(x)\phi^{(n-1)}(x) + \cdots + a_1(x)\phi'(x) + a_0(x)\phi(x) = f(x)
      </me>
    </p>
    <p> where the functions <m>a_0(x), \dots, a_{n-1}(x), a_n(x)</m> and <m>f(x)</m> are continuous
      on some interval <m>I</m>. </p>

  </introduction>


</section>